'''Asita''' or '''Kaladevala''' was a [[hermit]] [[asceticism|ascetic]] of [[History of India|ancient India]] in the 6th century BCE. He is best known for having predicted that prince Siddhartha of [[Kapilavastu (ancient city)|Kapilavastu]] would either become a great [[chakravartin]] or become a supreme religious leader; Siddhartha was later known as [[Gautama Buddha]].<ref name="Narada2006">{{cite book|author=Narada|title=The Buddha and His Teachings|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eTUpDwAAQBAJ|date=1 January 2006|publisher=Jaico Publishing House|isbn=978-81-7992-617-8|page=3-4}}</ref>

